hide v1.0

Syntax: hide [-s] | [-h] | [-d DEST] | [-D] | [-a] | [-A] | [-i] | [-r]

Options:
  -s SHOW       Show the files of the current profile
  -h HIDE       Hide the files of the current profile
  -d DEST       Change the current destination
  -D SHOW DEST  Show the current destination
  -a AUTO hide Enable/disable Auto hide: show/hide based on the current state
  -A SHOW AUTO  Show if auto hide is enabled/disabled
  -i INFO       Show hide info page (Only really useful when Auto hide is enabled)
  -r DEFAULTS   Restore hide to defaults

hide is a tool to easily show or hide files from a certain directory.